WEEK 4

Day 1
On this day, I will learn the basic concept of OSINT or Open-Source Intelligence. I will understand how information from public sources can be used for research, cybersecurity, and investigations. I will also learn the importance of using legal and ethical methods when gathering information online.
During this activity, I will explore simple examples of public information that can be found on websites and social media platforms. This will help me understand how people and organizations leave digital traces on the internet.

Day 2
Basic Website Investigation
For this day, I will practice simple ways to gather information from websites. I will learn how to look at a website and identify useful details such as the organization name, contact information, and other publicly available data. I will also try basic domain lookups to see when a website was created and who owns it. This activity will help me understand how much information can be found from a public website.

Day 3
Image Search Practice
On this day, I will practice using reverse image search tools to find where images appear online. I will upload or search for an image and see if I can find the original source or other websites that use the same image. I will also observe small details in photos such as buildings, signs, or landscapes that may help identify where the image was taken.

Day 4
Checking Public Data Breaches
For this activity, I will learn how to check if an email address has appeared in a public data breach. I will use publicly available tools to understand how breaches expose information and why password security is important. This will help me understand the risks of reused passwords and the importance of protecting personal accounts.

Day 5
Basic Social Media Research
On this day, I will practice looking at public social media profiles to gather basic information. I will observe profile details, posts, and connections that are publicly visible. This activity will help me understand how people leave digital footprints online and how information can be collected from open sources.

Day 6
OSINT Challenge Practice
For this day, I will complete several OSINT challenges for practice and skill development. These challenges will involve analyzing images, searching public records, and using different OSINT techniques to discover hidden information.
During the challenges, I will apply the OSINT process by first identifying what information the challenge is asking for. After that, I will collect data from open sources such as search engines, maps, and archived pages. I will then analyze the clues and verify the findings using multiple sources before documenting how I reached the final answer.
These challenges are meant for learning and fun while allowing me to practice the techniques I learned throughout the course, such as reverse image searching, geolocation, username searching, and advanced search operators.
My write-ups will explain the steps I followed, the tools I used, and how I verified the results.
